post.description:
This API endpoint allows you to execute a decision for a specific key using an HTTP POST request to {{host}}/deployment/decision/execute/:key.

### Request Body

The request should include a raw JSON payload with the following structure:

``` json
{
    "input": [
        {
            "variable": "",
            "value": "",
            "type": ""
        }
    ]
}

 ```

- `variable`: The name of the variable.
- `value`: The value of the variable.
- `type`: The type of the variable.


### Response

Upon successful execution, the API returns a JSON response with a status code of 200 and a Content-Type of application/json. The response body has the following structure:

``` json
{
    "code": "",
    "data": {
        "output": [
            {
                "variable": "",
                "type": "",
                "value": ""
            }
        ]
    },
    "message": ""
}

 ```

- `code`: The status code of the response.
- `output`: An array containing the output variables with their types and values.
- `message`: Any additional message related to the execution.

