This endpoint allows you to update the layout for a specific deployment identified by the code in the URL. The HTTP PUT request should be made to {{host}}/deployment/layout/:code, where :code is the identifier of the deployment layout to be updated.

The request should include a JSON payload in the raw request body type, with the following structure:

``` json
{
  "code": "",
  "value": {
    "id": "",
    "code": "",
    "name": "",
    "label": "",
    "styles": {
      "width": "",
      "height": ""
    },
    "children": [
      {
        "id": "",
        "name": "",
        "label": "",
        "props": {},
        "styles": {},
        "component": "",
        "properties": {
          "align": "",
          "colSpan": "",
          "justify": ""
        }
      }
    ],
    "component": "",
    "properties": {
      "align": "",
      "gutter": 0,
      "justify": ""
    }
  }
}

 ```

The response to the request will have a status code of 200 and a JSON content type. The response body will have the following structure:

``` json
{
  "code": "",
  "data": {
    "code": "",
    "id": 0
  },
  "message": ""
}

 ```

The "data" field contains the updated code and id of the deployment layout, while the "message" field may provide additional information about the request execution.

